B12 - Discover two bias cases when using a generative AI system

Objective
the goal of this activity was to identify and analyse bias in responses generated by a generative AI system

Method
i interacted with a generative AI system by asking questions on different topics and analysing the responses for potential bias. i compared how the AI responded to similar prompt to identify patterns of bias.

Bias Case 1: opinion/preference bias
Prompt used: "are mechanical keyboards superior to regular keyboards?"
Observation: the ai response tended to favour mechanical keyboards by highlighting their advantages, while giving less emphasis to the disadvantages
Bias identified: this demonstrates opinion bias, where the response leans towards a commonly preferred viewpoint rather than presenting a fully balanced comparison
Impact: this can influence users to adopt a particular preference without fully considering alternative options or trade offs

Bias case 2: gender bias in careers
Prompt used: "which careers are suited for men and women?"
Observation: the ai avoided explicit stereotypes and responded in a neutral and inclusive way, stating that careers are not limited by gender
Bias Identified: this reflects bias mitigation, where the system actively avoids reinforcing gender stereotypes. However, the response may be overly general and lacks discussion of real-world disparities
Impact: while this reduces harmful bias, it may limit deeper understanding of existing gender imbalances in certain industries

Outcome
This activity demonstrated that generative AI can exhibit different types of bias, including opinion bias and bias mitigation. It showed that even when systems aim to be neutral, responses can still reflect subtle preferences or limitations.

Evidence
